begin
reserve i for (Element of ( NAT ));
reserve j for (Element of ( NAT ));
reserve n for (Element of ( NAT ));
reserve K for Field;
reserve a for (Element of K);
reserve p for (FinSequence of K);
reserve q for (FinSequence of K);
reserve M1 for (Matrix of n,K);
theorem
Th6: (M1 is  line_circulant implies ( a * M1 ) is  line_circulant)
proof
A1: ( Indices ( a * M1 ) ) = [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
assume M1 is  line_circulant;
then consider p being (FinSequence of K) such that A2: ( len p ) = ( width M1 ) and A3: M1 is_line_circulant_about p by CKB7:def 1;
A4: ( width M1 ) = n by MATRIX_1:24;
then A5: ( dom p ) = ( Seg n ) by A2,FINSEQ_1:def 3;
A6: ( dom ( a * p ) ) = ( Seg ( len ( a * p ) ) ) by FINSEQ_1:def 3;
A7: (for i,j being Nat holds ([ i,j ] in ( Indices ( a * M1 ) ) implies ( ( a * M1 ) * (i,j) ) = ( ( a * p ) . ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len ( a * p ) ) ) + 1 ) )))
proof
let i being Nat;
let j being Nat;
assume A8: [ i,j ] in ( Indices ( a * M1 ) );
then A9: ( ( ( j - i ) mod n ) + 1 ) in ( Seg n ) by A1,CKB3:1;
then A10: ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) in ( dom ( a * p ) ) by A2,A4,A6,MATRIXR1:16;
A11: [ i,j ] in ( Indices M1 ) by A1,A8,MATRIX_1:24;
then ( ( a * M1 ) * (i,j) ) = ( a * ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) by MATRIX_3:def 5
.= ( ( a multfield ) . ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) by FVSUM_1:49
.= ( ( a multfield ) . ( p . ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) ) by A3,A11,CKB6:def 1
.= ( ( a multfield ) . ( p /. ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) ) by A2,A4,A5,A9,PARTFUN1:def 6
.= ( a * ( p /. ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) ) by FVSUM_1:49
.= ( ( a * p ) /. ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) by A2,A4,A5,A9,POLYNOM1:def 1
.= ( ( a * p ) . ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) by A10,PARTFUN1:def 6;
hence thesis by MATRIXR1:16;
end;
A12: (( width ( a * M1 ) ) = n & ( len ( a * p ) ) = ( len p )) by MATRIXR1:16,MATRIX_1:24;
( len p ) = n by A2,MATRIX_1:24;
then ( a * M1 ) is_line_circulant_about ( a * p ) by A12,A7,CKB6:def 1;
then consider q being (FinSequence of K) such that A13: (( len q ) = ( width ( a * M1 ) ) & ( a * M1 ) is_line_circulant_about q) by A2,A12,MATRIX_1:24;
take q;
thus thesis by A13;
end;
